r 20 minutes. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Steak and kidney filling"},{"content":"Place oil and onion into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add beef, kidneys and carrot and cook <b>5 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add flour, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, stock paste, water, salt and pepper and cook <b>60 min\/90°C\/\/speed <b>."},{"content":"Add mushrooms and cook <b>15 min\/90°C\/\/speed <b>."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"Grease a 1L pudding basin (ensure basin fits comfortably into Varoma dish - see Tips) with butter. Roll out three-quarters of the pastry into a circle (30 cm, approx. 5 mm thickness). Line pudding basin with pastry, then trim off edges. Roll out remaining pastry into a circle large enough to cover top of basin. Cover lined basin and pastry lid with plastic wrap, then place into refrigerator until ready to use (see Tips)."},{"content":"Using a slotted spoon, transfer filling into lined basin, leaving a 1 cm gap at the top. Pour gravy over filling, to pastry edge, and reserve remaining gravy for serving. Brush pastry rim with water. Place pastry lid over gravy and firmly press edges together all the way around to seal."},{"content":"Place a large circle of baking paper loosely over pastry lid. Cover baking paper with a large circle of aluminium foil. Tie a piece of kitchen string loosely around basin to secure paper and foil, allowing space for pastry to expand during cooking. Place basin into Varoma dish."},{"content":"Place 1800 g of the water into mixing bowl. Place Varoma into position, secure Varoma lid and steam <b>60 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add remaining 400 g water, secure Varoma lid and steam for a further <b>60 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Remove Varoma and allow pudding to stand for 5 minutes. Carefully remove foil and paper from pudding basin, then invert pudding onto a plate. Cut into wedges and serve with reserved warmed gravy."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Suet mix is a combination of beef suet and aerated flour. It's often used in puddings and dumplings, and can be found at most major supermarkets.","Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> or the <i>Everyday Cookbook<\/i> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","Ensure your pudding basin fits comfortably in the Varoma dish; the Varoma lid must close securely.","To save time, grease and line your pudding basin with pastry while the filling is cooking. Cover and store in refrigerator until needed.","Both pastry and filling can be made well in advanced and either frozen or stored in refrigerator for up to 3 days before assembling and cooking. Alternatively, pudding can be assembled in the basin, then frozen. Place pudding into refrigerator for 24 hours to defrost before cooking as per recipe."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","3h 45m","6 portions"]}